    {
      "text": "`import { FastMCP } from \"fastmcp\"`",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_table",
      "tool_name": "FastMCP",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "`import { EdgeFastMCP } from \"fastmcp/edge\"`",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_table",
      "tool_name": "EdgeFastMCP",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "stdio, httpStream, SSE",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_table",
      "tool_name": "Transport",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "Stateful or stateless",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_table",
      "tool_name": "Sessions",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "Built-in `authenticate` option",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_table",
      "tool_name": "OAuth/Authentication",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "If true, indicates the tool does not modify its environment",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_table",
      "tool_name": "false",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "If true, the tool may perform destructive updates (only meaningful when `readOnlyHint` is false)",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_table",
      "tool_name": "true",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "If true, calling the tool repeatedly with the same arguments has no additional effect (only meaningful when `readOnlyHint` is false)",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_table",
      "tool_name": "false",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "If true, the tool may interact with an \"open world\" of external entities",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_table",
      "tool_name": "true",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "Any OAuth 2.0 provider",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_table",
      "tool_name": "fastmcp",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "- Simple Tool, Resource, Prompt definition",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Features",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "Configure your `wrangler.toml`:",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Deployment",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "[Tools](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/concepts/tools) in MCP allow servers to expose executable functions that can be invoked by clients and used by LLMs to perform actions.",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Tools",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tools can log messages to the client using the `log` object in the context object:",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Logging",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "The errors that are meant to be shown to the user should be thrown as `UserError` instances:",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Errors",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tools can report progress by calling `reportProgress` in the context object:",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Progress",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "[Resources](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/concepts/resources) represent any kind of data that an MCP server wants to make available to clients. This can include:",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Resources",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "[Prompts](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/concepts/prompts) enable servers to define reusable prompt templates and workflows that clients can easily surface to users and LLMs. They provide a powerful way to standardize and share common LLM interactions.",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Prompts",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "FastMCP supports OAuth 2.1 authentication with pre-configured providers, allowing you to secure your server with minimal setup.",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Authentication",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "The `session` object is an instance of `FastMCPSession` and it describes active client sessions.",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Sessions",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "`FastMCPSession` represents a client session and provides methods to interact with the client.",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "FastMCPSession",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "`requestSampling` creates a [sampling](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/concepts/sampling) request and returns the response.",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "requestSampling",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "`requestSampling` accepts an optional second parameter for request options:",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Options",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "The `clientCapabilities` property contains the client capabilities.",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "clientCapabilities",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "The `loggingLevel` property describes the logging level as set by the client.",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "loggingLevel",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "The `roots` property contains the roots as set by the client.",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "roots",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "The `server` property contains an instance of MCP server that is associated with the session.",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "server",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
    {
      "text": "- FastMCP is inspired by the [Python implementation](https://github.com/jlowin/fastmcp) by [Jonathan Lowin](https://github.com/jlowin).",
      "source": "punkpeye/fastmcp",
      "method": "readme_heading",
      "tool_name": "Acknowledgements",
      "label": 0,
      "licence": "mit"
    },
